Three separate auto crashes have allegedly claimed the lives eight persons in Kwara State. The crashes, which involved six petrol tankers and a car, occurred around Olooru-Kanbi in Moro Local Government Area of the state. The incidents were said to have happened between Tuesday evening and early hours of Wednesday. An eyewitness account revealed that the crash occurred when one of the tankers heading for the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC) depot at Oke-Oyi in the Ilorin East local government, had a head-on collision with another coming from the same depot. It was also gathered that another tanker, loaded with diesel also collided with another coming from Jebba, also in Moro local government area of the state. A private car was badly impacted in the crash, sources said. A combined team of officers and men of the Fire Service, police and the Federal Road Safety Commission (FRSC) were promptly drafted to the scene of the accident for the rescue operation.